| **Routing**         | React Router (data mode)                          | 7.13        |
| **Styling**         | CSS Modules + PostCSS Nesting + design tokens     | —           |
| **Icons**           | lucide-react                                      | 0.575       |
| **Components**      | `@my-monorepo/components` (shared library) + clsx | —           |
| **i18n**            | i18next + react-i18next (PL / EN)                 | 25 / 16     |
| **SEO**             | react-helmet-async                                | 3.0         |
| **Markdown**        | react-markdown                                    | 10.1        |
| **Backend**         | NestJS                                            | 11          |
| **ORM**             | Prisma (driver adapter: `@prisma/adapter-pg`)     | 7           |
| **Database**        | PostgreSQL                                        | 17          |
| **Cache**           | Redis                                             | 7           |
| **Tests (web)**     | Vitest + Testing Library                          | 4.0         |
| **Tests (backend)** | Jest                                              | 30          |
| **Linting**         | ESLint (flat config)                              | 10          |
| **Language**        | TypeScript (strict, ESM)                          | 5.9         |
| **Runtime**         | Node.js                                           | 22          |
| **Reverse proxy**   | nginx                                             | 1.27        |
| **Containers**      | Docker + Docker Compose v2                        | —           |
| **CI/CD**           | GitHub Actions → GHCR                             | —           |
| **Hosting**         | Mikrus VPS + Cloudflare Full (strict)             | —           |

## Monorepo structure

```
my-monorepo/
├── apps/
│   ├── web/          # React 19 SPA (Vite) — home page + blog
│   ├── backend/      # NestJS 11 API — Prisma + PostgreSQL + Redis
│   └── cms/          # (placeholder) future Markdown-based CMS
├── packages/
│   ├── components/   # @my-monorepo/components — shared UI components
│   └── styles/       # @my-monorepo/styles — design tokens, themes, base CSS
├── infrastructure/
│   ├── compose/      # Docker Compose: dev, prod-local, prod-server
│   ├── nginx/        # Reverse proxy (Dockerfile + configs)
│   ├── postgres/     # Init scripts for PostgreSQL
│   └── redis/        # Redis configuration
└── scripts/          # Helpers: compose orchestration, docker-check, favicon generator
```

## Application features

### Web (frontend)

| Feature            | Description                                                             |
| ------------------ | ----------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Home page**      | Hero section, projects section, promotional section                     |
| **Blog**           | Paginated article list, single article view (Markdown), per-article FAQ |
| **i18n**           | Full bilingual support (PL / EN), persisted in `localStorage`           |
| **SEO**            | Dynamic meta tags per route (`react-helmet-async`)                      |
| **Design system**  | CSS Modules + semantic tokens from `@my-monorepo/styles`                |
| **Navigation**     | Navbar, blog sidebar with category tree, breadcrumbs                    |
| **Responsiveness** | Mobile drawer on blog, layout stacking at breakpoints                   |

### Backend (API)

| Endpoint             | Description                  |
| -------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| `GET /`              | Health check                 |
| `GET /redis-test`    | Redis connectivity test      |
| `GET /postgres-test` | PostgreSQL connectivity test |

The backend is in its base phase — `DatabaseService` (Prisma + pg pool) and `RedisService` are ready for expansion.

## Requirements

- Node 22, pnpm 10, Docker + Compose v2

## 1. Local (dev)

```bash
git clone git@github.com:adamzagorski92/turbo-adam.git
cd turbo-adam/my-monorepo
pnpm install
pnpm compose:dev up            # nginx :8080, web :5173, backend :3000, postgres, redis
```

Open `http://localhost:8080`.

Stop: `pnpm compose:dev down`

Optionally — expose DB/Redis ports to host:

```bash
pnpm compose:dev up --expose   # postgres :5432, redis :6379
```

## 2. Local (prod-like)

```bash
cp .env.prod.local.example .env.prod.local   # set POSTGRES_USER/PASSWORD/DB + DATABASE_URL
pnpm compose:prod up                          # http://localhost:8080
```

## 3. Deploy to Mikrus (production)

Full guide: [DEPLOYMENT.md](my-monorepo/DEPLOYMENT.md)

Summary of steps:

1. Create a `deploy` user on the server, configure SSH.
2. Configure Cloudflare (DNS AAAA + Full strict + Origin Certificate).
3. Upload SSL certificates to the server (`/var/lib/turbo-adam/certs/`).
4. Set secrets in GitHub Actions (see table below).
5. Push to `master` → workflow automatically builds images and deploys.

### GitHub secrets

| Secret                     | Value                                        |
| -------------------------- | -------------------------------------------- |
| `DEPLOY_HOST`              | Server IPv6 or hostname                      |
| `DEPLOY_PORT`              | SSH port (on Mikrus usually 5-digit)         |
| `DEPLOY_USER`              | `deploy`                                     |
| `DEPLOY_SSH_KEY`           | Private key for GitHub Actions               |
| `DEPLOY_APP_DIR`           | `/var/lib/turbo-adam`                        |
| `POSTGRES_USER`            | e.g. `admin`                                 |
| `POSTGRES_PASSWORD`        | strong password                              |
| `POSTGRES_DB`              | e.g. `monorepo_db`                           |
| `PGADMIN_DEFAULT_EMAIL`    | PgAdmin login e-mail                         |
| `PGADMIN_DEFAULT_PASSWORD` | PgAdmin password                             |
| `PGADMIN_PORT`             | _(optional, default 5050)_ PgAdmin host port |
| `DEFAULT_SITE_URL`         | Site URL for SEO (used at web image build)   |
| `GHCR_PAT`                 | _(optional)_ GitHub PAT with `read:packages` |

### Verification

```bash
curl -I https://app.your-domain/
```

## Architecture

```
Client → :443 → nginx ─┬─ /api/* → backend:3000 (NestJS)
                        └─ /*     → web:80 (React SPA static)
```

### Docker networks (dev)

```
public  (nginx ↔ web ↔ backend)
private (backend ↔ postgres ↔ redis)   [internal]
```

Details: [DEPLOYMENT.md](my-monorepo/DEPLOYMENT.md)
